<TITLE> 5 killed in lightning </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kurigram, May 17 (bdnews24.com)  Five people were killed and two others injured in a lightning at Nageshwari upazila in Kurigram on Monday. The dead were identified as Hajra Begum (37), wife of Badiar Rahman, and her son Mehedi Hasan Rhidoy (5), Maqbul Hossain (36), 'Hafizul' (30) and Amjad Hossain (40) of Khorardara village under Ramkhana union of the upazila. Injured Mansur Ali (35) and Rabbani (30) were admitted to a Nageshwari hospital. Ramkhana union chairman Sahidur Rahman said that the storm started at around 8am. Some people were working in a rice field beside the house of Badiar, he said. They took shelter in a hut with corrugated iron sheet for roof. A lightning struck the roof at around 8:30am leaving Badiar's wife and son and three workers dead on the spot, the chairman said. Badiar was not at home at that time. bdnews2
